            <div><b>Case Study1: Applying a natural capital approach to Fisheries Management Plan</b></div>
            MMO and Defra are developing England’s first natural capital-based Fisheries Management Plan (FMP) for pelagic fisheries in the south-west and Celtic Sea. This is using the best practice guidance for taking a natural capital approach that MMO developed through mNCEA. This includes taking a partnership approach to co-develop the plan, with industry, policy makers, regulators, eNGOs and other stakeholders who can influence, or are impacted by fisheries management, in the area. Developmental evaluation has indicated the success of the approach in building a collaborative partnership that has delivered an evidence-based, shared understanding of the wider system that affects and is affected by the state of pelagic fish stocks and their management in the FMP area. Together, the partnership has developed a clear set of legally binding time-bound actions that will lead to better outcomes for the FMP fish stocks, their ecosystem and the people whose livelihoods depend on them.
        </p>                                        
