            Volunteer Seabirds at Sea (VSAS) is a citizen science initiative which recruits and trains volunteers to collect high quality seabirds at-sea data from vessels of opportunity around the UK. JNCC’s Marine Birds project expanded the Volunteer Seabirds at Sea (VSAS) monitoring programme into England, building new citizen science volunteer networks and utilising existing ferry routes to capture high quality marine bird data.
